The paper deals with communication complexity, which is a topic in theoretical computer science (cs.CC). The problems studied in the paper, sparse set disjointness and exists-equal, involve sets and vectors, respectively, which are common data structures in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also uses information theory techniques to analyze the communication complexity of the problems (cs.IT). Additionally, the paper involves combinatorial and probabilistic arguments, which are often used in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.LG).
